                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: rgb(255,255,255);"><b>                              <span style="font-size: 25px;">                                Estate and Collector Car Auction                                <a href="https://www.proxibid.com/asp/Catalog.asp?aid=124287"                                  target="_blank" style="float: right;">                                <img src="images/pblogo_lg.png"></a>                              </span>                              </b></p><br><br>
                              <p style="margin-bottom: 0px; color: white;">                                <span style="color: rgb(255,255,255);">                                  <b><span style="font-size: 18px;">Held on                                    March 25, 2017 at 8095 Darling St. Salem, OR</span>                                  </b>                                <span style="font-size: 20px;
                                  color: rgb(218,197,152); float: right;">
                                  This is a NO RESERVE AUCTION</span>
                                <br><br>
                              <a href="#auctionDetails">IMPORTANT Auction Details</a>
                              <br><br>
                              <a href="#map">CLICK HERE for Travel Accommodations</a>
                            <br><br>                              <h3 style="color: white;"><a href="documents/LotCatalog.pdf" target="_blank">Click Here to view a PDF of the Lot Catalog</a></h3>                              <br><br>
                            <p style="color: white;">
                            Over 40 years ago a man with a passion for the cars
                            that were built when he was a boy began to collect.
                            Over the years he enjoyed all of the cars from the
                            1930&apos;s, 1940&apos;s, 1950&apos;s, and
                            1960&apos;s. All were Chevrolet&apos;s both cars and
                            trucks. There were many landmark historical events
                            that forever shaped our country the stock market
                            crash of 1929 and 50% unemployment. Drought first
                            hit the country in 1930. By 1934, it had turned the
                            Great Plains into a desert that came to be known as
                            the Dust Bowl. 1939 to 1945 saw our country in the
                            throws of WWII and as early as 1955 some of our
                            boys began to visit the jungles of Vietnam which of
                            course lasted to 1975. Our cars went from wood
                            frame to steel bodies, from boxy sedans to
                            streamline coupes and then shoe box gas misers.
                            <br><br>
                            Our client collected it all from barns and shops
                            all over America and on March 25, 2017 we will at
                            auction be offering his collection to collectors
                            all over the world. Below you will find a list of
                            vehicles offered and as we put this collection
                            together to offer it this list will be adjusted and
                            fine tuned into the final catalog that will be used
                            for the sale. Listed now below is the original list
                            we were given by the family and we will be adding
                            more detail as we get closer to the sale day we
                            have found that some vehicles were sold so some
                            adjustments need to be made. There are 3 barns and
                            garages on the property and about 50% of the list
                            has been stored in the barns for many years. There
                            are many original parts, body parts, engines,
                            fenders, bumpers, grills, hoods, doors, dash parts,
                            wheels, beds, axles  and over 50 radios and their
                            trim these will all be added as we lot them up. If
                            you have any questions please feel free to contact
                            me via email at <a href="mailto:dan@cappint.net">
                              dan@cappint.net</a> or call me at
                            <a href="tel:503-720-5580">503-720-5580</a> between
                            8am and 6pm West Coast Time. </p>
