                    <a href="../html/gallery.php">CLICK HERE TO VIEW PHOTOS
                    </a><br><br><h4 class="white">We accept Visa, Mastercard, American Express.</h4></span></p>                    <br>                    <div class="white">                      <h4>We will be using Proxy Bid for our Live Bidding the day of the auction.                        <br>Click on their logo below to be directed to their website</h4>                    <a href="https://www.proxibid.com/asp/Catalog.asp?aid=124287"                      target="_blank">                      <img src="images/pblogo_lg.png"></a>                    </div>                    <br><br>                      <div id="auctionDetails" class="white">                        <h2 class="white">Auction Details</h2>                        <br>                        <p class="white">Welcome to our Estate and Collector Car & Truck Sale.                          This is a very unique sale and will be held on site in one ring on one day.                          We will make our announcements at 8:45am. Bidding will start at 9am.                          We will start with the shop and household items, followed by the cars and trucks,                          and finally, end with the automotive parts.                          This will be an all day event so we will have food on site and restrooms.                          We anticipate wrapping it up around 4 - 5 PM.                          We are anticipating only an hour for load out after the sale so planning to pick up your items on Sunday may be a good idea.                          <br><br>                          All items at this sale are sold <strong>&quot;AS IS WERE IS AND NO WARRANTIES ARE EXPRESSED OR IMPLIED. YOU ARE ENCOURAGED TO SEEK PROFESSIONAL ASSISTANCE IN THE APPRAISAL OF CONDITION OF ALL ITEMS THAT YOU INTEND TO BUY. ALL SALES ARE FINAL. YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR REMOVAL UNDER THE TERMS EXPLAINED IN THIS ANNOUNCEMENT AND RELATED COSTS.&quot;</strong>                        </p>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic;">&quot;NO SMOKING IS ALLOWED ANYWHERE ON THE SITE. SMOKING IS ALLOWED ON THE MAIN ROAD OFF THE PROPERTY. IF YOU ARE SMOKING ON THE SITE YOU WILL BE ASKED TO PUT IT OUT OR LEAVE&quot;</strong></h4>                        <br>                        <h4 class="white"><strong>Only the automotive items will be available for bidding online at <a href="https://www.proxibid.com/asp/Catalog.asp?aid=124287" target="_blank">ProxyBid</a></strong></h3>                        <br>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Event time line:</strong></h4>                        <ul class="white">                          <li>We will be starting at 8:45am with announcements. The auction will begin with the shop and household items at 9AM. There are approx. 250 lots and it will take about 2.5 hours to complete.</li>                          <li>PLEASE NOTE THE SHOP AND HOUSEHOLD ITEMS WILL NOT BE OFFERED TO ONLINE BIDDERS.</li>                          <li>When this is finished we will begin to sell the vehicles at between 11:30 and noon. This would be lots 1000 thru 1060.</li>                          <li>When we are done with these lots we will begin with lot number 1 and go through lot 750 which are the auto parts. There are a number of open lots here so it will go quickly.</li>                        </ul>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Payment:</strong></h4>                        <ul class="white">                          <li>All items must be paid for before the end of the day (5pm) on March 25th (sale day)</li>                          <li>We will accept Cash or Visa. If you are planning on a larger purchase we will accept your personal or business check but you will not be able to remove your items until your check has cleared our bank and funds are deposited. Wire transfers are able to be made but again items cannot be removed until funds are deposited.</li>                          <li>A 10% BUYERS PREMIUM APPLIES TO ALL SALES</li>                          <li>IF YOU PAY WITH CREDIT CARD A 13% BUYERS PREMIUM WILL APPLY</li>                          <li>IF YOU PURCHASE ANY LOT THAT CANNOT BE &quot;HAND CARRIED&quot; OFF THE PROPERTY THERE WILL BE A &quot;RIGGING FEE&quot; for removal&ast;</li>                        </ul>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">REMOVAL INFORMATION</strong></h4>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">We will be open on day of sale until 6pm. There will be limited check out on day of sale. You can hand carry your items out with stamped paid receipt. If you need to load out items due to size or need help from the rigger please line up as instructed on the road out side the sale site. 3 vehicles at a time will be allowed in to remove items.</strong></h4>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Please hurry and load so others can access the site.</strong></h4>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Remember, if you cannot lift it you need to talk to the rigger for help loading and related fees.</strong></h4>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">On Sunday we will be open from 9AM until 6PM. Monday March 27th thru Friday March 31st of the week after the sale we will be there from 9AM till 5PM. Same rules apply to site access as sale day three vehicles allowed on site at a time. We will be removing the tent at about 9am.</strong></h4>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Appointments will need to be arranged with the rigger to remove all other items. All items not removed by Friday March 31 (unless other arrangements have been made with rigger) will be resold or disposed of.</strong></h4>                        <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">To schedule appointments to have items removed for you see the folks at the riggers desk on sale day to schedule an appointment.</strong></h4>                        <p class="white">To remove items from the site you will need to have paid for the item and have your receipt stamped paid.</p>                        <h5 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic;">DO NOT LOSE YOUR RECEIPT YOU WILL NEED IT FOR ALL REMOVAL. YOU MUST BRING YOUR OWN HELP FOR LOADING OUR STAFF WILL ALL BE BUSY WITH CHECK OUT AFTER THE SALE. YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE</strong></h5>                        <br><br>                        <p class="white">There are 4 specific areas that the sale is conducted in and that will have items that will be sold.<br>                          <ul>                            <li>The house garage will be all Estate items. When the sale is complete in that area the doors will be closed until the end of the sale. This is for security reasons. At the end of the sale there will be staff there to check your ticket and make sure that the correct lots go out with the correct buyers.</li>                            <li><strong>Building 1</strong> This includes the shop area which has tools, hardware and other items. The 3 end bays of this building are all automotive items. When the sale is complete in that area the doors will be closed until the end of the sale. This is for security reasons. At the end of the sale there will be staff there to check your ticket and make sure that the correct lots go out with the correct buyers.</li>                            <li><strong>Building 2</strong> Just the end of the building will be open and it has wood products that will be sold with the Estate and Shop items. When the sale is complete in that area the doors will be closed until the end of the sale. This is for security reasons. At the end of the sale there will be staff there to check your ticket and make sure that the correct lots go out with the correct buyers.</li>                            <li><strong>Building 3</strong> This would be the car barn again nothing will be removed until after the sale is complete. These are some of the last items to sell so we will have staff available to watch all of the items to insure nothing is removed prior to the end of sale.</li>                            <li>The yard around building 3 there are many hand carry items here and a lot of items that need to be rigged. As we sell these items we will have staff monitoring this area.</li>                          </ul>                          <br>                          We have a situation at this sale that constitutes an issue with removal and that is the wet ground that we have to deal with and the ingress and egress. There is only one way in and one way out and if it rains it will turn into a swamp down by the barns. Also the property is for sale and the family has asked us not to tear up the passage from the house to the barns. We also have a time limit of one week for removal. To manage this we have decided to work with a rigger for all non hand carry removal. This is an unusual situation but it must be to preserve the integrity of the property so here are the rules:<br>                          <ul>                            <li>There are two types of lots sold at this Auction <strong style:"text-decoration: underline;">&quot;HAND CARRY&quot;</strong> and <strong style:"text-decoration: underline;">&quot;RIGGED&quot;</strong></li>                            <li><strong style="font-style: italic;">HAND CARRY - This is defined as any item that a person can pick up by them selfs or with help that you provide and walked to your parked vehicle.</strong></li>                            <li><strong style="font-style: italic;">RIGGED - This will be the case with all non HAND CARRY ITEMS.</strong> Examples would be Cars that are not running, Motors, Frames, Cabs, Cars that are running but will be driven off site, etc.</li>                          </ul>                          <h4 class="white"><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">RIGGED ITEMS: YOUR RECIPT MUST SHOW YOU HAVE PAID FOR THE RIGGING FEES BEFORE YOU HAVE THE RIGGER MOVE OR LOAD THE ITEMS.</strong></h4>                          <ul>                            <li>SMALLER RIGGED ITEMS WILL BE LOADED DIRECTLY ONTO YOUR TRUCK OR TRAILER STAGED IN THE FEILD NEXT TO THE SITE.</li>                            <li>LARGER RIGGED ITEMS WILL BE either scheduled to be delivered to your location by the rigger or moved and staged in the field in the parking area by the rigger for your pickup.</li>                            <li>Rigging immediately after the sale will be determined by the rigger and accessibility after the sale.</li>                            <li>Smaller items such as motors will not be staged in the field but must be place directly on your trailer or truck by the rigger.</li>                          </ul>                          <h3 style="text-decoration: underline; font-style: italic;"><strong>PLEASE REMEMBER THERE WILL BE AN EXTRA FEE APPLIED TO ALL ITEMS BOUGHT THAT CAN NOT BE MOVED BY HAND. PERSONAL VEHICLES WILL NOT BE ALLOWED ON THE SITE PAST BUILDING NO.1</strong></h3>                          <br>FOR QUESTIONS CALL DAN <a href="tel:503-720-5580">503-720-5580</a>                          <br><br>ALL ITEMS MUST BE REMOVED NO LATER THAN 7 DAYS AFTER SALE.                        </p>                      </div>                      <br><br>                      <div id="map">                        <iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=1V_wz2pWekmE7PLV6KptY8CpUINk" width="100%" height="480"></iframe>                      </div>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
